{
  "stem": "24195.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, the fire was so that you couldn't breathe anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The oxygen became sparse, and it just fueled more fires.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We went to a high rise bunker where there was-- near the zoological garden in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was like 10 stories high or maybe higher, and that was like a refuge to get there for all the people that were bombed out.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We stayed there for about two nights.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They always had panic in that bunker too because they had anti-aircraft batteries stationed on top of that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the bombers hit the-- they hit the bunker.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They couldn't penetrate them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They couldn't penetrate.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was such a strong cement building, you know, that you couldn't penetrate it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But they did hit the batteries.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the vibration of the-- even, you know, down on the ground floor was bad enough so that people almost started to become panicky and started to rush towards the exits of the-- there was-- of the bunker and started to almost being trampled upon and people falling down.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I noticed that the German Air Force soldiers that were part of this aircraft battery, they came out with their pistols drawn and trying to keep the crowd back from panicking anymore.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then the next day, we went to-- there were still trains going out of Berlin, although most of the train stations were bombed out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we-- we went to Silesia, which is now part of Poland, because we had friends there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were-- and tried to stay there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What did you use for money?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How did you travel?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, we had money.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
